
Overview of noun hike

The noun hike has 3 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                           
1. (2) hike, hiking, tramp -- (a long walk usually for exercise or pleasure; "she enjoys a hike in her spare time")
2. rise, boost, hike, cost increase -- (an increase in cost; "they asked for a 10% rise in rates")
3. raise, rise, wage hike, hike, wage increase, salary increase -- (the amount a salary is increased; "he got a 3% raise"; "he got a wage hike")

Overview of verb hike

The verb hike has 2 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                           
1. (1) hike, hike up, boost -- (increase; "The landlord hiked up the rents")
2. hike -- (walk a long way, as for pleasure or physical exercise; "We were hiking in Colorado"; "hike the Rockies")
